 Here is a Java solution to check if an integer n is a power of 3 without using loops or recursion:

```java
public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        return (n & (n - 1)) == 0; 
    }
}
```

The idea is to check if n is a power of two by seeing if n & (n - 1) is zero. This is true if n is a power of two, since the only way n & (n - 1) can be zero is if n is a power of two.

Then, we can test if n is a power of three by checking if it is a power of two and then checking if it is a multiple of 3. This allows us to check if n is a power of three without loops or recursion.

